<a href="javascript:card_browser(113)">Nazgul Sword</a> x2    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> ***Site Path***<br>
<P><P><br>
{1} Prancing pony<br>
{2} Bree Streets<br>
{3} Ford of Bruinen<br>
{4} Moria Lake<br>
{5} The new bridge<br>
{6} Valley of the Silverlode<br>
{7} Silverlode Banks<br>
{8} Anduin Banks<br>
{9} Sumit of Amon Hen<br>
<br>
Sorry about that.  Thanks Casey.<br>
<br>
***End of update<br>
<br>
<br>
Ok, here&#39;s the thing.  There is a common saying around the game.  Your fellowship makes the deck. It doesn&#39;t matter what your shadow side does, if your fellowship can&#39;t survive and move fast, you are dead.  I believe this to be true.  Here&#39;s what you do to start.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Bid 1.  Always.  No more, no less.  Why?  Well, If you bid one, you get to go first over those who bid zero. If you bid 2, you can&#39;t pull Aragorn and safely get around Nazgul Swords.  3 is right out since you will go to 4 if you don&#39;t draw Aragorn opening hand. Toldea killing Legolas this early is very bad.  You have NO burden removal in this deck.  You don&#39;t need it.  Trust me.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Ok, always go first if you have the option. Which you usually do.  No matter what, you should always be able to run to the sanctuary first turn.  You never give THAT much shadow first round and your fellowship should hold out.  The only exception is Nagul with a bunch of blade tips and Black breaths out first site. If you have an ARV then you should be just fine.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
If you know they aren&#39;t playing Nazgul, then you should map for almost all of your sites. Usually 3, 6 (definitley), 7 (Definitley), 8 (maybe), 9(definately).  Basic concept for the fellowship is to get everyone tooled up quickly and surgically take out minions.  Never play all five companions until site 6+.  If they are running Uruk-hai and you don&#39;t have gift of boats out or your site 6, then don&#39;t drop sam until site 7. Savagery to match their numbers is not good with only 4 people.  If they are playing moria, you can drop him at site 4.  He&#39;s funny when he goes def +1 and takes on a cave troll and balrog, then stealths it.  Goes again for fierce battle and stealths again.  <br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
You want to get your allies working soon.  Secret Sentinels is key.  Kills sauron/moria and gets rid of Spies of Saruman. Gift of boats lets you run from 6-9 if you need to.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Rags now.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Very simple.  Slow your opponent down to a crawl.  Kill them if you can, but you just want to keep them to 1 site a turn.  A little bit of ARV protection is included with Not easily Destroyed.  You can heal during the Maneuver phase.  Great combo with Enqeua if they have 5 burdens.  Exert, heal, exert, heal.  You get the idea.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Over all game tip advice.  Unless you need it the very next round, pitch it. cycling through your deck is very powerful. No strangers pretty much kills Uruk-hai with token choke. As well as the archery. If you have a fully healed Aragorn at site nine and an exertable Sam, then that is pretty much game. Use the mirror every chance you get, a discarded minion is always the easiest minion to kill.  He&#39;s already dead.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Mad Props to Courtney Haggerty fr building this deck.  Madder Props for Casey Barson taking it to the Utah TOC and going 7-1 and winning with it. I went 6-2 because I&#39;m an idiot.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Mad slops go to Courtney Haggerty for playtesting against this deck with his tournament deck and losing twice, but still going to the tournament with it.  If it gets beat a couple time before the tournament, you shouldn&#39;t play it in the tournament.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Some card ommissions:<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
No elrond.  Not worth the 4 shadow cost.  Can&#39;t count of getting Galadriel first.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
No Boromir.  Having 5 companions is bad against uruk-hai. Don&#39;t really need him.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
No gandalf I have plenty of condition control. Don&#39;t need Servant.  He&#39;s too many card slots<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
